    <!-- ============== HELP ============== -->
    <section id="help" class="page">
      <div class="page-header">
        <div>
          <div class="page-title">❓ Help & Jobs</div>
          <div class="page-subtitle">Every job explained. Every task, laid out. Click to expand.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <details open>
          <summary>🔎 The Researcher — What is the job?</summary>
          <p>Researchers find investment ideas worth considering. Think of yourself as a detective: you dig through filings, news, and data until you know a company so well you could explain it to a 5th grader.</p>
          <strong>Your tasks:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Read the 10-K.</b> It's the company's annual report. Skim the "Business" and "Risk Factors" sections first.</li>
            <li><b>Build a 1-page pitch.</b> Company → Product → How it makes money → Why buy now → Risks.</li>
            <li><b>Compare to 2 competitors.</b> How is this company different?</li>
            <li><b>Present at the weekly meeting.</b> Keep it to 3 minutes.</li>
          </ul>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>💰 The Investor — What is the job?</summary>
          <p>Investors take research and make real decisions. You're responsible for <i>when</i> we buy, <i>how much</i>, and <i>when</i> to sell.</p>
          <strong>Your tasks:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Review pitches.</b> Ask hard questions. "What could make this wrong?"</li>
            <li><b>Vote with the group.</b> Final buys happen by majority.</li>
            <li><b>Set position size.</b> Never more than 20% of portfolio in one stock as beginners.</li>
            <li><b>Execute the trade</b> on our paper-trading platform.</li>
            <li><b>Write a 3-line thesis</b> in the Investments tab for every buy.</li>
          </ul>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>📊 The Market Analyst — What is the job?</summary>
          <p>Analysts track the big picture. Stocks don't move in a vacuum — interest rates, inflation, and sector trends matter.</p>
          <strong>Your tasks:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Weekly market brief.</b> What happened in the S&P 500, Nasdaq, and Dow this week?</li>
            <li><b>Watch earnings season.</b> Alert the club when portfolio companies report.</li>
            <li><b>Track Fed news.</b> Rate hikes move everything.</li>
            <li><b>Flag risk.</b> If a sector looks shaky, say so.</li>
          </ul>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>📝 The Secretary — What is the job?</summary>
          <p>The Secretary is the club's memory. Without you, meetings vanish and good ideas get lost.</p>
          <strong>Your tasks:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Log every meeting</b> in the Meeting Logs tab. Title, date, attendees, notes.</li>
            <li><b>Take live notes</b> during the meeting.</li>
            <li><b>Send a 5-line recap</b> to the group after meetings.</li>
            <li><b>Track attendance.</b></li>
            <li><b>Schedule next meeting</b> before this one ends.</li>
          </ul>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>🏦 The Treasurer — What is the job?</summary>
          <p>The Treasurer owns the numbers. If the Investor decides and the Researcher discovers, the Treasurer measures.</p>
          <strong>Your tasks:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Log every trade</b> in the Investments tab the day it happens.</li>
            <li><b>Update prices weekly</b> so returns stay current.</li>
            <li><b>Compare to S&P 500.</b> Use the Benchmark section of the Investments page.</li>
            <li><b>Update Goals progress</b> when goals are hit.</li>
            <li><b>Report P&L</b> at every meeting (win or lose — honesty matters).</li>
          </ul>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>👑 The President — What is the job?</summary>
          <p>The President sees everything, asks the hardest questions, and keeps the club moving.</p>
          <strong>Your tasks:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Review every group's work weekly.</li>
            <li>Answer members' questions on the "Ask the President" tab.</li>
            <li>Manage membership and funds on the protected President page.</li>
            <li>Set the semester's theme / goals with the group.</li>
          </ul>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>🛡️ The Vice President — What is the job?</summary>
          <p>The Vice President is the President's right hand — same access, same responsibilities when the President can't be there.</p>
          <strong>Your tasks:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Step in for the President in any meeting they miss.</li>
            <li>Help review every group's weekly work.</li>
            <li>Co-answer questions on the "Ask the President" tab.</li>
            <li>Share the load on managing roster, goals, and funds.</li>
            <li>Access the Leadership control panel with your personal access code.</li>
          </ul>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>🧭 New member? Here's your first week.</summary>
          <ol>
            <li>Read this Help page.</li>
            <li>Pick a role on the Roles tab.</li>
            <li>Open a paper trading account (Resources tab).</li>
            <li>Attend one meeting and take notes for yourself.</li>
            <li>Do your first task — check it off in the Tasks tab.</li>
          </ol>
        </details>
      </div>
